The '''Cytotoxic hazard symbol''' is a [[hazard symbol]] consisting of a [[triangle]] with the letter "C" inside it. It is used to label [[biomedical waste]] bags and containers.<ref>http://www.sterihealth.com.au/services/medical-waste-collection/cytotoxic-waste</ref>

Cytotoxic waste, the [[by-product]] of [[Cytotoxicity|cytotoxic]] [[drug therapy]] administered to patients (such as [[chemotherapy]]), typically includes all drug administrative [[equipment]] (e.g. needles, syringes, dripsets etc.) as well as all gowns and body fluids/waste from patients undergoing such treatment.

