{{Multiple issues| {{primary sources|date=May 2008}} {{orphan|date=February 2009}} }} '''Working in Partnership Programme''' (WiPP)<ref name=WIPP>{{cite web|url=http://www.wipp.nhs.uk|title=Website of the Working in Partnership Programme|publisher=}}</ref> was launched in [[England]] in 2004 under the new [[General medical services|General Medical Services]] (nGMS) contract to support doctors in general practice by providing them with innovative ideas on how to improve services for the public.
